Hi,

I recommend the following workaround instead...

std::vector<some_type> _your_favorite_list;

_your_favourite_list.push_back(_whatever_);
_your_favourite_list.push_back(_whatever_);
_your_favourite_list.push_back(_whatever_);
_your_favourite_list.push_back(_whatever_);
_your_favourite_list.push_back(_whatever_);

Rcpp::List = Rcpp::as<std::vector<some_type> >(_your_favourite_list);


Best regards,
Tama Ma




